doc.after: Effective February 15, 2007, the FAA ruled that US-registered twin-engined airplane operators can fly more than 180-minute ETOPS to the design limit of the aircraft. In October 2014 EASA certified the Airbus A350XWB to 370-minute ETOPS,[5] while Boeing is planning to certify its 787 to 330-minute ETOPS.[6]
